function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` function from Julia's standard library. The anonymous function `w -> isuppercase(w[1])` checks if the first character of each word `w` is an uppercase letter using the `isuppercase` function. The `filter` function returns a new vector containing only the words that satisfy this condition.
